"use strict";(self.webpackChunkweslley_io=self.webpackChunkweslley_io||[]).push([[8584],{2793:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"route":"talks","tag":"Curitiba","articles":[{"title":"Codecon Summit \u2014 Embrace the Hacker Way","slug":"codecon-summit-embrace-the-hacker-way","date":"2025-07-19","authors":["Weslley Ara\xfajo"],"tags":["BR","PR","Curitiba"],"content":"\\n\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Creating a Test Runner: What happens behind the tests?\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nThere\'s a lot of talk about testing, but what\'s it like to create a test runner from scratch?  \\nMore than that: how do you test a test runner?\\n:::\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nIn this talk, I break down Poku, the only Brazilian _test runner_ for **JavaScript** and **TypeScript**, which challenges more than 14 years of language history by bringing native **JavaScript** syntax to tests.\\n\\nYou\'ll learn about the power of subprocesses, isolation, and the advantages of working with concurrency\u2014all using only native language features.\\n\\nWait, native syntax?\\n\\nYou\'ll discover the history of testing in **JavaScript** and why tests don\'t follow the natural flow of the language, while uncovering the inner workings of the most popular _test runners_.\\n\\nThis is the kind of insight that, regardless of which _tester_ you use, will change the way you truly see testing.\\n","filePath":"codecon-summit.mdx","mdxPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/07/19/codecon-summit.mdx","summary":[],"description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Creating a Test Runner: What happens behind the tests?\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nThere\'s a lot of talk about testing, but what\'s it like to create a test runner from scratch?  \\nMore than that: how do you test a test runner?\\n:::","social":"./banner.jpeg","socialPath":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/07/19/banner.jpeg","readingTime":1,"lastModified":"2025-12-20T21:22:28.000Z","authorsData":[{"name":"Weslley Ara\xfajo","title":"Active open-source contributor, Microsoft MVP, MySQL2\'s maintainer and Poku\'s creator \u2728","url":"https://weslley.io/en/","image_url":"/img/avatar.png","socials":{"linkedin":"wellwelwel","github":"wellwelwel","instagram":"wellwelwel","youtube":"weslleyio"}}],"previousArticle":{"title":"DevConverge LATAM & Oracle \u2014 SPRINT SP","slug":"devconverge-latam-%26-oracle-sprint-sp","description":"\ud83c\udf99\ufe0f **Talk:** Inventing the New: The Meeting Point Between Human Creativity and AI-Assisted Generation\\n\\n:::note Summary\\nImproving performance in a legacy system is part of the routine. Inventing algorithms and a brand-new architecture is something completely different.\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/08/09/banner.jpeg"},"nextArticle":{"title":"Winx Day (Luciano dii Souza \u2014 O Primo Dev)","slug":"winx-day-luciano-dii-souza-o-primo-dev","description":"\ud83d\udcf9 **Live (Talk):** Overcoming impostor syndrome and the challenges of existing in the market through open source.\\n\\n:::info\\nAn online event organized by [**Luciano dii Souza**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/lucianodiisouza/), with a relaxed approach and held through the [**Discord**](https://discord.gg/wyrRdpGKmj) community for developers, aiming to share experiences and knowledge, especially for those who are just starting in the field.\\n:::","social":"/home/runner/work/weslley.io/weslley.io/i18n/en/talks/2025/06/14/banner.png"}}]}')}}]);